 Position Type 
 Full Time 
 The Grassroots Leadership & Engagement Coordinator collaborates with the Youth and Student Program Manager and the Community Program Manager to build, strengthen and support Amnesty International USA’s Membership Programs. The Youth & Student Program provides young people with the opportunity to engage in human rights education, advocacy and organizing in their communities across the United States, while the Community Program provides opportunities for community members to lead and organize human rights education and activism in their communities across the country. The Grassroots Leadership & Engagement Coordinator is responsible for managing key projects within these two programs, providing support to existing community-based groups, youth and student chapters, and membership networks, developing systems and processes for data management and tracking, developing and implementing communication strategies, and carrying out outreach to target audiences. They are further responsible for the annual registration process of AIUSA student and youth groups and the annual census of community-based local groups, identification of new growth and scaling opportunities, and effective mobilization around days of action and other organizing initiatives. 
 
 Essential Job Functions 
 Implement membership strategies that support retention, engagement, and growth in both Community and Youth & Student Programs 
 Support the development and maintenance of Human Rights Education, Youth & Student, and Community Programs’ web pages, social media channels, contact lists, electronic communications, and AIUSA’s online events calendar 
 Coordinate development, procurement, distribution and tracking of materials to AIUSA groups 
 Monitor, assess, and test communication strategies that increase engagement 
 Collect and assess demographic information and other data related to our grassroots participants and apply findings to initiatives to grow a diverse membership 
 Develop and facilitate webinars, trainings and orientations for Community and Youth & Student Programs based on data on member needs and interests 
 Develop and distribute resources and support to Community and Youth & Student Program groups and member networks, and follow up on activities to ensure compliance with AIUSA policies and procedures 
 Track group activity using outcome mapping tools and produce impact reports and infographics 
 Coordinate and execute annual membership renewal initiative and identify opportunities to market and promote membership to potential new members 
 Identify and implement digital methods for growing a sense of community among our AI groups across the country 
 Respond to inquiries from various stakeholders 
 
 Youth & Student Program Specific Responsibilities: 
 Coordinate annual group registration and ongoing data collection and upkeep for AIUSA student groups 
 Support as needed in implementing AIUSA’s National Week of Student Action and other Youth & Student Program initiatives 
 Manage member communication through the Slack workspace for AIUSA student groups 
 
 Community Program Specific Responsibilities: 
 Coordinate annual local group census and ongoing data collection and upkeep for AIUSA community program networks 
 Support as needed in implementing AIUSA’s National Banned Books Week and other Community Program sponsored initiatives 
 
 Desired Qualifications 
 Highly organized and results driven 
 Experience or interest in community organizing and intersectional movement building 
 3-5 years’ experience with outreach, activism, organizing and/or program coordination; work on human rights or social justice preferred 
 Exercises commitment to inclusion, diversity, equity, and accessibility 
 Experience in working to build intergenerational spaces 
 Experience managing multiple concurrent projects to success 
 Demonstrated ability to develop and implement systems or processes for a team 
 Experience working with a database system and/or other data management and digital organizing tools 
 Ability to conduct research, gather data, analyze information, and prepare reports and other materials 
 Strong written communication ability, including experience with email, newsletters, toolkits, and/or promotional materials 
 Demonstrated capacity to get things done independently as well with others 
 Ability to develop presentations and facilitating workshops and trainings 
 Experience working with volunteers and/or within a membership-based organization 
 Fluent in Microsoft Office and Google Suite applications 
 Experience in WordPress and web design a plus 
